# Naming conventions

## Files & directories

| Item | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Directories | `kebab-case` | `apps/api/`, `packages/db/` |
| TypeScript source files | `kebab-case.ts` | `github-webhook.ts`, `pipeline-run.service.ts` |
| React component files | `PascalCase.tsx` | `RunDetailPage.tsx`, `WorkspaceSwitcher.tsx` |
| Test files (unit) | colocated `*.test.ts` or `*.spec.ts` | `github-webhook.test.ts` |
| Test files (integration) | `*.integration.test.ts` | `runs.integration.test.ts` |
| Markdown docs | `PascalCase` or `kebab-case` per existing | `PipeWatch_MVP_PRD.md` |
| Env variable names | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` | `JWT_SECRET`, `PIPEWATCH_EDITION` |
| Public client env | `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix | `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` |

## Code identifiers

| Item | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| TypeScript types & interfaces | `PascalCase` | `PipelineRun`, `WorkspaceRole`, `Integration` |
| TypeScript variables & functions | `camelCase` | `verifyWebhookSignature`, `getActiveWorkspace` |
| Constants | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` | `DEFAULT_RETENTION_DAYS`, `JWT_EXPIRY_SECONDS` |
| React components | `PascalCase` | `<RunCard />`, `<PipelineStatusBadge />` |
| Hooks | `useCamelCase` | `useWorkspace`, `useSseStream` |

## Database (Decision #37 — vendor-neutral)

- Model names: `PascalCase` (`Workspace`, `Integration`, `PipelineRun`, `PipelineJob`)
- Table names: `snake_case` (`workspaces`, `integrations`, `pipeline_runs`, `pipeline_jobs`, `pipeline_steps`)
- Column names: `snake_case` (`workspace_id`, `external_run_id`, `created_at`)
- Provider IDs: `external_*` prefix (`external_installation_id`, `external_run_id`, `external_job_id`)
- Enum values: lowercase or `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` per column — match Drizzle schema
- Migration names: Drizzle Kit generates timestamps — **never create migration directories by hand**

## Product vocabulary

| ✅ Correct | ❌ Forbidden (in schema/API) |
|---|---|
| `workspace` | `organization`, `org`, `tenant` |
| `integration` | `github_app` (as table/type name) |
| `pipeline_run` / `PipelineRun` | `workflow_run` (in DB/API types) |
| `pipeline_job` / `PipelineJob` | `workflow_job` (in DB/API types) |
| `repository` / `repositories` | `repo` (in API resource names) |
| `PipeWatch CE` / `PipeWatch Cloud` | inconsistent edition naming |
| `member` (workspace role) | `user` (when referring to workspace membership) |

UI copy may say **"workflow"** when referring to GitHub Actions terminology (PRD §4.5).

## Domain areas (issue summaries, commit scopes, bug prefixes)

`Workspaces` · `Integrations` · `Repositories` · `Pipelines` · `Runs` · `Webhooks` · `Auth` · `Billing` · `SSE` · `Insights` · `Onboarding` · `Dashboard` · `API` · `Marketing` · `CE` · `CI` · `Infra` · `Worker`

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// ❌ GitHub-specific table name
interface WorkflowRun { ... }     → ✅ interface PipelineRun { ... }

// ❌ file naming
GithubWebhook.ts                  → ✅ github-webhook.ts
run_card.tsx                      → ✅ RunCard.tsx
```
